<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/phytokeys.136.38558.figure2>
    dc:description "Figure 2. Illustration of Tryssophyton quadrifolius (A-G) and T. merumense (H, I). A Habit (right view in flower) B young flower with anthers inflexed C flower with anthers erect and petals fallen D shorter antepetalous anther, dorsal E longer antesepalous anther, dorsal F longer anther, lateral G young fruit H habit I capsular, 3 - merous fruit. Sources: A-G Wurdack 5865 H Radosavljevic 165 I Wurdack 5870 (all US)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/363662" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

